net.opentsdb.core

Interface iRowSeq

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DataPoints, Iterable<DataPoint>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RollupSeq, RowSeq

    public interface iRowSeq
extends DataPoints
    An interface that defines methods implemented by row sequence implementations that represent a row of data in storage.
    Since:
    2.4

    • Nested Class Summary

      An interface for an iterator that all row sequences must implement.

    • Method Detail

      • setRow

        void setRow(org.hbase.async.KeyValue row)
        Sets the initial column in the sequence. The row must be empty and this must be called before addRow(KeyValue).
        Parameters:
        row - A non-null KeyValue representing a column in the row.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if setRow(KeyValue) or addRow(KeyValue) has already been called.

      • addRow

        void addRow(org.hbase.async.KeyValue row)
        Adds a column in the proper sequence in the row. Must be called after setRow(KeyValue) has been called.
        Parameters:
        row - A non-null KeyValue representing a column in the row.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if setRow(KeyValue) has not been called first.

      • key

        byte[] key()
        Returns the row key this sequence represents. May be null if setRow(KeyValue) has not been called.
        Returns:
        The row key for this sequence.

      • baseTime

        long baseTime()
        Returns the base time for the row in Unix epoch seconds.
        Returns:
        The base time for the row.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if setRow(KeyValue) has not been called.

      • internalIterator

        iRowSeq.Iterator internalIterator()
        Returns:
        an internal iterator for this row sequence.
